                            <comment id="13082391" author="jeremias@apache.org" created="Wed, 10 Aug 2011 15:17:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As can be read in the associated SVN commit, I&apos;ve replaced the Group3 1D decoder. The same problem can also occur with Group3 2D and Group4. So, eventually, PDFBox also needs implementations for these two. Especially Group4 is widely used which is why I&apos;m keeping this issue open for the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13948169" author="tilman" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 17:22:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed two of three decoders re fill bits. (I could fix the third one but would prefer to have a test file). Now there&apos;s only &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-457&quot; title=&quot;Invalid code encountered while decoding CCITT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-457&quot;&gt;PDFBOX-457&lt;/a&gt; left. It could be an EOL, but I can neither prove or disprove that theory. An EOL would make no sense in a G4 encoded document, at least according to wikipedia:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_4_compression&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_4_compression&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167394" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 19:49:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is good enough to count as &quot;fixed&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
